{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"53b05b6c-0d25-4cff-9c8a-22782aa21519","content":"Here's what I found:\n\n**`my_app/views.py:3`** — `datetime.now()`\n\n```python\nnow = datetime.now()\n```\n\nThis is a **hard-coded static call** that makes the function difficult to test because you can't control or predict the returned time.\n\n### Recommended fix\n\nUse Django's `timezone.now()` (timezone-aware) and inject it so tests can mock it:\n\n```python\nfrom django.utils import timezone\n\ndef index(request, *, _now=None):\n    now = _now or timezone.now()\n    return render(request, 'index.html', {'time': now})\n```\n\nOr, in tests, mock it with `freezegun` or `unittest.mock.patch`:\n\n```python\nfrom unittest.mock import patch\nfrom django.utils import timezone\n\nwith patch('my_app.views.timezone.now', return_value=fake_time):\n    response = index(request)\n```\n\n**Summary:** Only 1 file, 1 untestable static found. The project is small — this is an easy fix.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"1b41503c-7fdd-46bb-96cd-f81259f806dc","outputTokens":255,"requestId":"5C20:C4D03:41F7B9:5309DA:69F561DA"},"id":"3f7ffcdc-793e-4c09-917d-dd6b18eddfa5","timestamp":"2026-05-02T02:30:57.411Z","parentId":"b0318eb6-f16e-4ccc-b36b-105bbb12eecd"}
